txt.en: 'I saw you return with a number of our injured warriors to our lines. Your valour speaks well of you!'
'Quickly, let us be out of here before more arrive!'
'You came! I thought I would die out here.'
'It's not as bad as it looks. I can still fight a bit.'

Talk to Captain Féarn atop Dol Baran

The Dunlendings relentlessly harry the Rohirrim soldiers atop Dol Baran, affording them little chance to rest or recover their wounded. Several soldiers lie upon the battlefield, seemingly beyond aid.
'My thanks friend. I thought I was done for.'

'The Dunlendings have been attacking our positions for nearly three days...not in any great numbers, but in small bands, attacking and withdrawing, then sending fresh men into the fray.

'My own men are exhausted, and some have been caught away from our fortifications, suffering serious injuries. The Dunlendings have let them lie where they fell, hoping to draw us out.

'If you could find some way to rescue my fallen men, I would be indebted to you, for we are sorely put upon.'
'It seems my luck may not have run out quite yet, thanks to you.'
